																		Join us March 17 to explore DFIR triage, AI-powered response, and hard lessons from real investigations.

https://go.exterro.com/e/43312/mmit-utm-bmcr-source-FTKImager/ft52w2/2071178155/h/o-dwaj3G0bfxGTCVlB-LFFayxG76xXSYryGKMeWZSck

																		Hello Lorcan,

You downloaded FTK Imager — which means you care about getting evidence captured correctly, consistently, and defensibly.

If that’s your world — forensics, e-discovery, internal investigations, or security — we’d like to invite you to Exterro INFORM 2026, an all-day virtual, community-driven webinar series on March 17, 2026.

It’s education-first and built around the decisions that matter before deep analysis even begins.

A\A few sessions you’ll recognize immediately from an imager mindset:

	DFIR triage in the first hour: what to collect, what to preserve, and common early missteps that limit options later

	Modern threat reality: ransomware, insider activity, and hybrid environments — and how to stay structured and legally defensible

	Local, air-gapped LLMs for faster triage: accelerate early understanding while keeping sensitive data under your control

	Phishing to compromise: following the artifact trail, including remote access tools used post-click

	Security fundamentals that support recovery: identity, hypervisor, network, and backup resilience

Each hour stands on its own, so you can attend strategically without feeling behind.

Registration is open — secure your seat today:

 

